  "abstract": "Statistical information suggests a substantial increase in area under irrigation, under rice and wheat, and in use of chemical fertilizers in Asia.  However, a slowing down in growth of productivity of rice and wheat has been\r\nreported in recent times. In the past, legumes occupied a significant area in the Indo-Gangetic Plain (IGP) but the area has declined due to the more remunerative and relatively more stable cereals. However, legumes still have a potential role in sustaining productivity of rice- and wheat-based systems. Atmospheric nitrogen (N) fixed by legumes in symbiosis with root nodule bacteria potentially\r\nmeets much of the N demand of the legume and can contribute to the N requirements of subsequent crops...",
